"'''Lovin' is Really My Game'''" is a 1977 song by American group [[Brainstorm (US band)|Brainstorm]], and is the lead single from their debut album ''[[Stormin']]''. The song was written by lead singer, [[Belita Woods]] along with Tranita Womack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrolyrics.com/loving-is-really-my-game-lyrics-brainstorm.html |title=Brainstorm - Loving Is Really My Game Lyrics |website=MetroLyrics.com |date=2016-03-15 |accessdate=2016-10-13}}</ref> 

The extended version of the song was release as a vinyl 7" single in two parts; A-side part 1 and B-side part 2. "Lovin' Is Really My Game" peaked at number fourteen on both the Billboard Disco Play chart, and Hot Soul chart.<ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=41}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=74}}</ref>

