==Cover versions==
* In 1978, [[Betty Wright]] recorded a cover which was included on her ''Betty Wright, Live'' album.
* In 1984, Dance music performer, Zino, made the top 30, on the dance chart, with her recording.
* In 2000, [[Ann Nesby]] went to number one on the dance charts for one week with her recording.<ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=187}}</ref>
*Sylvester also covered this track.

